                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "efaa2de8e18640a392666",
                    "stepText": "Next, calculate the kinetic energy of the photoelectrons for the first case using the stopping potential. Multiply the electron charge $!$e = 1.602 \\times 10^{-19}~C$!$ by $!$V_s = 1.5~V$!$ to find $!$eV_1$!$ in Joules.",
